[ProMED-mail is very grateful to Dr D'Ortenzio and colleagues for this
interesting report. First-hand news from health care professionals in the
field and their supporting laboratories is particularly valuable. The
results of the chikungunya virus sequence comparisons will be of particular
interest, providing evidence of endemicity of the virus on the island or
its reintroduction. One hopes that the detection of chikungunya cases at
this time is not a harbinger of an outbreak later in the season.

A map showing the location of Reunion Island in the Indian Ocean can be
accessed at <http://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/africa/re.htm>. -
Mod.TY

Saint-Gilles-Les-Bains can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail
interactive map of Reunion Island at <http://healthmap.org/r/00JG>. -
Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]
